GURU

New GUI users can just click on the Desktop icon after installation to create a User_Report.txt file

CLI users can just execute the shell script like this:

/bin/sh User_Report.sh > Report_$(hostname)$(date +%F) && gzip Report_$(hostname)$(date +%F)


CLI users can access guru, via ssh onto the remote computer over the network. So you don't need a 'TigerVNC' or remote GUI desktop to easily use the Generate_User_Report application.


